          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix and bake, 12 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Line two baking trays with baking paper. Whisk the cooled {{coconut-oil}} with the {{light-brown-sugar}} and {{caster-sugar}} until combined. Add the {{oat-milk}} and {{vanilla-extract}} and stir well. Add the {{plain-flour}}, {{bicarbonate-of-soda}}, and {{fine-sea-salt}} and mix until a dough forms. Fold in the {{chocolate-chips}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Roll into balls of about 25 g each and place on the lined trays, spaced 5 cm apart. Flatten each ball slightly with the palm of your hand. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes until the edges are set and pale golden but the centres still look soft. Leave to firm on the tray for 10 minutes before transferring to a rack.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
